HEADWORD: Talma
<hw>Tal"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Talmas</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Prob. so called from
<ets>Talma</ets>, a French actor.]</ety> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A kind of
large cape, or short, full cloak, forming part of the dress of
ladies.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A similar garment worn formerly by
gentlemen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Talmud</ent>⟦br⟧
